**Intuition**
Greedily always subtract the maximal roman number equivalent value from ```num```.

**Complexity**
- Time: O(1)
- Space: O(1)

**Implementation**
- C#
```
public class Solution {
    public string IntToRoman(int num) {

        if(num < 1)
            throw new ArgumentException("Invaid Input.");

        string[] roman = new string[]{"M","CM","D","CD","C","XC","L","XL","X","IX","V","IV","I"};
        int[] nums = new int[]{1000,900,500,400,100,90,50,40,10,9,5,4,1};

        string res = "";
        int i = 0;

        while(num > 0)
        {
            while(num >= nums[i])
            {
                res += roman[i];
                num -= nums[i];
            }            
            i++;  
        }

        return res;
    }
}
```

