class Solution {
public:
    string intToRoman(int num) {
        vector<int> values{1,4,5,9,10,40,50,90,100,400,500,900,1000};
        vector<string> roman{"I","IV","V","IX","X","XL","L","XC","C","CD","D","CM","M"};
        int idx=roman.size()-1;

        string ans;
        while(num>0){
            while(num<values[idx])
                idx--;
            int count=num/values[idx];
            num=num-count*values[idx];
            while(count--){
                ans+=roman[idx];
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

**Time Complexity:** 
O(1) as num is limited to 3999 only. 
O(n) if num is very very large and we need add "M" to string multiple times (Not given in constraints).

Why O(1) ? 
Reason - In worst case it will take constant(3) calls for some values[i] and value size is also constant to 13. 
So runtime will be < 13 * 3 only => *O(39) ~ O(1)*

