# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thougStringhts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Create two arrays, one to store the Roman numerals and the other to store their corresponding values.
2. Initialize a StringBuilder to store the Roman numeral representation of the integer.
3. Iterate over the arrays in parallel.
4. While the integer is greater than or equal to the value at the current index of the values array, append the Roman numeral at the corresponding index of the notations array to the StringBuilder.
5. Decrement the integer by the value at the current index of the values array.
6. Repeat steps 4 and 5 until the integer is less than the value at the first index of the values array.
7. Return the String representation of the StringBuilder




