# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The problem requires us to find all the words in the given words list that can be formed using the letters present on the given board matrix. We can use the Trie data structure to efficiently search for words in the given board

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The approach taken in the solution is to first build a Trie using the words list, and then perform a depth-first search (DFS) on the board matrix to find all the valid words.

The Trie data structure is built using the insert function, which inserts a word into the Trie by creating a new node for each character in the word. The search function checks if a given word exists in the Trie by traversing the Trie and checking if the end node of the word contains the word itself. The startsWith function checks if a given prefix exists in the Trie by traversing the Trie until the end of the prefix.

The findWords function initializes an empty set result, builds the Trie using the words list, and initializes a boolean matrix visited to keep track of the visited cells in the board matrix. It then performs a DFS on each cell in the board matrix, starting with an empty string str, and checks if the current prefix str exists in the Trie. If it does, it checks if str is a valid word by checking if the end node of str contains the word itself. If it is a valid word, it adds str to the result set. Finally, it marks the current cell as visited, and recursively performs DFS on its neighboring cells, adding the current cell's character to the str prefix.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(M(4⋅3^(L−1))), where M is the number of cells in the board, L is the maximum length of a word, and 4⋅3^(L−1) is the maximum number of child nodes in the Trie

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
 O(N), where N is the total number of characters in the words list, which is used to build the Trie.

# Code
