# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We use the trie data-structure to store all the words, and iterate over the same to search for words in the board. 
Note: No pruning is done, just simple plain algorithm! :)

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Main Algorithm:- 
1. Create an unordered set 
2. Create a trie data-structure and store all the words in it
3. Now iterate through each cell in the word and see if any word starts from it in trie
    3.1 if it does, then call a search function for that letter node in trie
4. Create an answer vector and copy the set to it
5. retur the answer

Search() algorithm:-
1. Store the char at current position in board and replace it with some temperory symbol like dollar ( this is done to avoid multiple traversals through the same branch ) 
2. If the current word is complete, add it to the answer set
3. Now for each of the four sides of current cell (right, above, left, below) - if it matches with next child of trie node, call function search on it recursively
4. replace the current position in board with its original symbol


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(m*n*m*n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(w*l)
    where w=number of words, and l= average length of a word
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

