**Algorithm Overview**
Dfs generates all string possible starting in each char of board, if any string matches then it is added to solution.

**Optimizations**
Using dfs for all possible string causes tle. So, max length of input string is found is used to limit the dfs calls.

**Code**
```cpp
class Solution {
    // stores words in a map, so that lookup in dfs can be done in O(1) time
    unordered_set<string> mp;
    // global state is used for easy insertion of ans by dfs
    vector<string> ans;
    // stores the maximum length of string
    int mx;

void dfs(vector<vector<char>>& board,int i,int j,vector<vector<bool>>& visit, string &word){ 
    if(i<0 || j<0 || i>=board.size() || j>= board[0].size()) return ;
    if(visit[i][j] || word.length() >= mx)return ;

    word.push_back(board[i][j]);

    // if mp contains the word, it is added to the answer
    // also, word is removed imediately from the map, to prevent duplicates
    // in answer
    if(mp.count(word)){
        ans.push_back(word);
        mp.erase(word);
    }

    //dfs calls
