this solution is like the top [solution](https://leetcode.com/problems/word-search-ii/discuss/59790/Python-dfs-solution-(directly-use-Trie-implemented).) from OldCodingFarmer with an extra trick (TLE - 10% -> 80% - 100%).

The idea is to count the number of words with a specific prefix in the Trie.
Then at remove time, we traverse the Trie and delete a node if it has a count of 1 (the path contains only the word we want to remove).

This makes the DFS run way faster (since it will know earlier if a path doesn't contain any word).

comment out the line `root.remove(s)` to see the effect of this optimization.

code:

