Code Explanation->we have added fake nodes or balloons with value 1 so that we dont have to check for out of bound error again and again.
k is the length of the interval .
why is it kept in outer bracket because once we pop a balloon the length of subparts will decrease by 1 atleast,
so solutions of smaller interval are needed.
now j is the starting point of the interval and so naturally j+k is the endpoint 
now we consider each balloon to be popped last and use the solution to the solved subproblem
Now explaining the dp recurrence relation->
dp[left][right]=max(dp[left][right],dp[left,i-1]+dp[i+1,right]+nums[i]*nums[left-1]*nums[right+1]);
the first term of max is a no brainer.However the second term implies that if we knew that ith was the last burst balloon .like for ex nums=[1,2,3,4,5]
and we are calculating dp[1,3](0 based indexing) and we knew that 2nd index element is the last balloon so in the end nums =[1,3,5] so popping 3 (2nd index element ) would yield product of nums[left-1] which is nums[0]=1 , nums[right+1] which is nums[4]=5 and nums[2]=3
so before breaking into subparts we take this factor nums[i]*nums[left-1]*nums[right+1] into consideration.

