solutions.content:
On first time when I saw this problem, I think that we came with the intuition :
1. We will burst all the ballon.
2. And for each ballon we can have two options:
      1. Either I can burst it or,
      2. I can skip it.


But this intuition got failed after looking at some hints. I tried to figure out that :

Let’s suppose we are going to burst the ballon in the range [left….right] so,

1. This range can vary from 0...N.
2. For each [left, right], we will burst every ballon and get the possible maximum coins for this [left, right]
3. In such a way, we have explored all the ranges of bursting the ballon and we required the range from [left=1… right=n] i.e. full length.

So,

1. My, Dp[left][right] = {Will tell you that what will be the maximum coins if you burst all the ballon from left to right.}
2. Let’s suppose we bursting i-th ballon :
3. So we’ll get the coin :
4.  `(dp[left][i-1] + dp[i+1][right]) + (nums[burn] * nums[left - 1] * nums[right + 1])`
5.  **dp[left][i-1] + dp[i+1][right] :** total coin from [left… right] after burning i-th ballon will be  coins of [left...i] and coins[i+1...right] because nums[i] is going to be burned plus coins what we will get extra after burning i-th ballon(i.e. nums[i] * nums[left - 1] * nums[right + 1])


```

class Solution {
   public:
    int maxCoins(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        nums.insert(nums.begin(), 1);
        nums.push_back(1);
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 2, vector<int>(n + 2, 0));

        // Let's extract from small length to n
        for (int len = 1; len <= n; len++) {
            for (int left = 1; left <= n - len + 1; left++) {
                // Get the right range
                int right = left + len - 1;
                int bestCoin = 0;

                // Find the maximum possible coins if we burned all the ballon in the rand left to right
                for (int burn = left; burn <= right; burn++) {
                    // total coin from [left...burn-1] and [burn+1...right] because [burn] is going to be burned
                    int coins = dp[left][burn - 1] + dp[burn + 1][right];
                    coins += (nums[burn] * nums[left - 1] * nums[right + 1]);
                    bestCoin = max(bestCoin, coins);
                }

                // Store the answer
                dp[left][right] = bestCoin;
            }
        }

        // return the max coins which getting after burning from 1-n
        return dp[1][n];
    }
};


